properties.NAME: Gainesville
properties.Title and Description:
Ordinance No. 180678: Prohibits the sale and use of plastic straws from food and retail establishments, along with special events at city facilities.

Approval vote will be held at the next City Commission Meeting.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged beverages with plastic straws; medical or dental facilities; hospitals; nursing homes or assisted living facilities; and those who require or rely on the use of a straw.
properties.Enforcement: Civil citation in accordance with Chapter 2, Article V, Division 6.
properties.Status: Pending, awaiting 1st reading in June, with effective date of January 2020.

properties.NAME: Surfside
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2018-1676: Prohibits the distribution, sale, or use of plastic straws and stirrers at any city facility, city property, commercial establishment, or by any special event permittee.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged drinks; medical or dental facilities; school district or county, state, or federal governmental entities; and those with a disability or other impairment requiring the use of a plastic straw.
properties.Enforcement: Violations shall be enforced through Chapter 15 of the Town code.

properties.NAME: Surfside
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Prohibits the distribution, sale, or use of single-use plastics (which include single-use plastic bags, single-use plastic flatware and dinnerware, and single-use plastic straws) by or in any commercial establishment, Town Facility, or Town Property or by any Special Event Permittee.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged drinks; medical or dental facilities; school district or county, state, or federal governmental entities; and those with a disability, impairment, or a religious belief requiring the use of a plastic straw.
properties.Enforcement: Penalties for violations shall be enforced through Chapter 15 of the Town code.

properties.Title and Description: Ordinance: No person shall distribute plastic straws within the Town
properties.Exceptions: Private property, School Board of Lee County, beverages prepared and packaged outside the Town
properties.Enforcement: Fines between $100- 500 for first time to third time offence within a year.

properties.Title and Description: Ordinance R5A: Prohibits the distribution, sale, or use of single-use plastics in any commercial establishment, including restaurants, hotels, retail stores, and condo and apartment buildings, and on Village Property and at Village-approved events.
properties.Exceptions: Medical and dental offices, as well as schools.
properties.Enforcement: Businesses will be fined $250 per infraction. Individuals can be fined $25 per infraction.

properties.NAME: Coral Gables
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2019-01: Amends the City of Coral Gables Code by creating a prohibition on the use of plastic straws and stirrers by city contractors; by Special Event Permitees; and on streets, sidewalks and other public places.
properties.Exceptions: Those with disabilities; small events (<100 attendees); and pre-packaged drinks.
properties.Enforcement: Extensive education campaign by the City for potential City Contractors and Special-Event Permitees.
properties.Notes: More information at the Skip the Straw Campaign, www.coralgables.com/skipthestraw

properties.NAME: Coral Gables
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2017-03: Prohibits the use of single-use carry out plastic bags by retail establishments and any entity or individual who has been issued a special event permit by the city.
properties.Exceptions: Medical prescription bags, garbage bags, clothes dryer bags, newspaper bags, pet waste bags. Residents can re-purpose carry out plastic bags.
properties.Enforcement: 12-month education period, then issuance of citations.

properties.NAME: Coral Gables
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2016-08: Prohibits city vendors or contractors in city facilities, special event permittees and their subconcontractors, and food service providers and stores from using, selling, or distributing polystyrene products,s uch as plates, bowls, cups, container lids, trays, coolers, ice chests, and food containers.
properties.Exceptions: Prepackaged food sealed prior to receipt by service provider; polystyrene used to store raw meat/seafood; Nonprofits, school district, governmental entities Does provide a financial hardship waiver for food service provider with annual gross income under $500,000 annually if there is no comparable alternative product and proof the purchase of the alternative would create undue financial hardship.
properties.Enforcement: Warnings issued for the first 180 days, then issuance of citations.

properties.NAME: Miami Beach
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance 2018-4205: Unlawful to carry single-use plastic straws or stirrers onto any beach or park within the city, or onto any city marina, pier, dock, or boat ramp, or for any business to provide plastic straws with the service or delivery of any beverage to patrons on any beach within the city.
properties.Exceptions: Individuals with a disability or medical condition that impairs the consumption of beverages without a single-use plastic beverage straw or single-use plastic stirrer
properties.Enforcement: Fines ranging between $100-$500.

properties.NAME: Miami Beach
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance 2017-4068: Prohibits the sale and use of expanded polystyrene (a.k.a Styrofoam) within the City and includes: parks, beaches, city-owned facilities, sidewalk cafes, special event permits, city marinas, unencapsulated docks, buoys, platforms, piers and boat ramps.
properties.Exceptions: Expanded polystyrene food service articles used for prepackaged food that have been filled and sealed prior to receipt by the food service provider or store; Expanded polystyrene food service articles used to store raw meat, pork, fish, seafood, or poultry sold from a butcher case or similar refrigerated retail display or storage case; The school district, and county, state, and federal governmental entities.
properties.Enforcement: Fines ranging between $100-$500.

properties.NAME: Miami Beach
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance 2018-4208: Prohibits the use/distribution of single-use carry out plastic bags on the right of way and to sidewalk cafe patrons.
properties.Exceptions: NA
properties.Enforcement: Fines ranging between $500-$1250.

properties.NAME: Pinecrest
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2018-14: Prohibits the distribution, sale, or use of plastic straws in any commercial establishment or by any mobile vendor, at any village facility, on village property or any other public property, or by any special event permittee.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged drinks; medical or dental facilities; school district or county, state, or federal governmental entities; and those with a disability or other impairment requiring the use of a plastic straw.
properties.Enforcement: Violations shall be enforced through section 2-174 of the code.
properties.Reference: Article VIII. - Prohibition on Distribution, Sale, or Use of Plastic Straws

properties.NAME: Pompano Beach
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance 2019-37: No person shall use plastic straws or sell, distribute, or offer for use on public beaches within city limits or in city parks or other city facilities. No person, food provider, beverage provider, or fast food service vendor shall provide a plastic straw to any customer. If the customer requests a single-use straw, they shall be provided with a single-use straw composed of renewable or compostable material, such as paper, sugar cane, or bamboo.
properties.Exceptions: NA
properties.Enforcement: NA

properties.NAME: West Palm Beach
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 4836-19: Prohibits the sale, distribution, or use of plastic straws and plastic stirrers in any commerial establishment within the city's jurisdictional limits or at any city facility or city property or by any special event permittee or city contractor.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged drinks; medical or dental facilities; school district or county, state, or federal governmental entities; and those with a disability or impairment requiring the use of a plastic straw.
properties.Enforcement: Penalities for violations shall be enforced through Chapter 26 of the City code.

properties.NAME: Hallandale Beach
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2018-027: Prohibits the distribution, sale, and use of plastic straws within city limits and on public beaches within city limits.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged drinks with plastic straws; medical and dental facilities; school district or county, state, or federal governmental entities; use during a locally declared emergency; and by those with a disability or other impairment requiring use.
properties.Enforcement: Fine of $100.

properties.NAME: Hallandale Beach
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2019: It is unlawful to use, bring, or distribute a single-use craay out plastic bag or expanded polystyrene food service article on public beaches within City limits.
properties.Exceptions: Medical and dental facilities; school district or county, state, or federal governmental entities; use during a locally declared emergency; and by those with a disability or other impairment requiring use.
properties.Enforcement: Fine up to $500.

properties.NAME: Hallandale Beach

properties.NAME: Hollywood
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance 97.05: Any establishment located east of the intercoastal Waterways selling food intended for consumption by customers off the premises of their business, is prohibited from using nonbiodegradable containers for serving food (and drink) products.
properties.Exceptions: NA
properties.Enforcement: 1st offense: $50 - $500, and/or jail up to 60 days, or both; 2nd offense: $75 - $500 fine; 3rd offense: $100 - $500 fine.
properties.Notes: More information can be found at https://www.hollywoodfl.org/1143/Plastic-and-Foam-Free-Beach.

properties.Title and Description: Policy and Procedure 137.2: Prohibits the use of single-use products, including, but not limited to, plastic straws, bags, and Styrofoam products, at city-owned parks, facilities, venues, and permitted events. In recognition of the needs of customers with disabilities, plastic straws may be provided upon request.
properties.Exceptions: Small events (<100 attendees) and pre-packaged foods and beverages.
properties.Enforcement: Revocation or cancellation of any permit for non-compliance with this policy.

properties.NAME: Delray Beach
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 10-19: Amends "Business Regulations" of the Code of Ordinance by adding a prohibition on single-use plastic straws. Upon adoption of the Ordinance, all restaurant and beverage establishments may distribute plastic straws only upon request of a patron. Starting January 1, 2020, restaurants and beverage establishments may not distribute plastic straws within the City.
properties.Exceptions: Those with a medical or physical condition for which non-plastic straws would be unsuitable; private property; school board; hospital or residential medical facility, such as a nursing home or assisted living; and pre-packaged beverages.
properties.Enforcement:
Beginning January 1, 2020:
1st offese within any twelve month period is punishable by a $100 fine. 2nd offense is a $200 fne. 3rd offense is a $500 fine.

properties.NAME: Largo
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. 2019-19: Prohibits the distribution and use of expanded polystyrene, Styrofoam, and polypropylene straws on public property to include temporary vendors on public property or entities engaged in a contractual relationship with the City.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged foods; any city contract, lease, or concession agreement entered into prior to the effective date of the ordinance; any temporary permit issued prior to the effective date of the ordinance; those with disabilities. Families who rent a pavilion in Largo parks.
properties.Enforcement: Violation will result in revocation of a special event permit

properties.NAME: St. Petersburg
properties.Title and Description: Starting January 2020, businesses will be prohibited from offering plastic straws.
properties.Exceptions: Those with a disability or other impairment requiring the use of a plastic straw.
properties.Enforcement: After January 1, 2020, civil citations, including warnings and fines, shall be issued.

properties.NAME: St. Petersburg
properties.Title and Description: City contractors, pushcart vending permittees, sidewalk cafe permittees, mobile food establishment permittees, food truck rally permittees, park permittees, outdoor public assembly permittees, and minor easement permittees shall not distribute expanded polystyrene products in conjunction with food or beverage services on City-owned property, or within or abutting the City right-of-way.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged foods and any city contract, lease, or concession agreement entered into prior to the effective date of the ordinance.
properties.Enforcement: After January 1, 2020, civil citations, including warnings and fines, shall be issued.

properties.NAME: Sarasota
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance will include an Upon Request policy on public properties including special events, sidewalk cafe permits, city leaseholds, and city facilities for any type of single-use straw.
properties.Exceptions: NA
properties.Enforcement: NA

properties.Title and Description: Ordinance will ban polystyrene, or Styrofoam, on public properties including special events, sidewalk cafe permits, city leaseholds, and city facilities
properties.Exceptions: NA
properties.Enforcement: NA

properties.NAME: Dania Beach
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description:
Ordinance No. 2018-07: No plastic straw shall be distributed in or from any restaurants and establishments that sell alcoholic beverages which are located adjacent to any navigable waterway located within the City, including the Atlantic Ocean, or at any City facility or City property or by any City special event permittee.

Exceptionsi include pre-packaged drinks; Broward County School Board; county, state, or federal governmental entities or those with disabilities.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged foods; schools; county, state, or federal governmental entities; and those who who suffer from disabilities.
properties.Enforcement:
First violation: $25 for individuals; $125 for commerical establishments

Second and subsequent violations: $50 for individuals; $250 for commercial establishments

properties.NAME: Fort Lauderdale
properties.Scope: City-owned property, Permitted events, Commercial establishments
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance No. C-19: Prohibits the sale and distribution of plastic straws within the City of Fort Lauderdale in or by any Commercial establishment or at any City Facility or City Property or by any Special Event Permittee.
properties.Exceptions: Pre-packaged beverages; medical or dental facilities; hospitals and property owned by the North Broward Hospital district; those who require or rely on the use of plastic straws; land or facilities owned and managed by the Broward County School Board; and during a locally declared emergency.
properties.Enforcement: Fine up to $500.
properties.Notes: Have started the More Flavor Less Plastic campaign to encourage reductions of more single-use plastics. More information at http://www.fortlauderdale.gov/lessplastic.

properties.NAME: Marco Island
properties.Title and Description: Ordinance: Prohibits the distribution, sale, or use of plastic straws at any business, restaurant, cafeteria, school cafeteria, cafe, bar, or other establishment, located directly adjacent to the city beaches and where food and/or drinks are served or purchased.
properties.Exceptions: Food grade paper straws; straws made of compostable plant material; and re-usable non-plastic straws.
properties.Enforcement: Fine up to $500.

properties.NAME: Martin
properties.Title and Description: Resolution No. 16-15.16: Supports the reduction of single use plastics by: Developing an outreach program to educate the public on the harmful impacts of plastics straws, polystyrene, and plastic products; reviewing the County's purchasing policies; encouraging businesses to use alternatives to plastic straws and stirrers; establishing a partnership with UF/IFAS and Surfrider; and encouraging Martin County residents and visitors to discontinue the use of platic straws and stirrers.
properties.Exceptions: NA
properties.Enforcement: NA

properties.NAME: Dade
properties.Title and Description: Resolution R-501-16: All products made from polystyrene, or Styrofoam, will be banned from County parks and beaches. This includes but is not limited to plates, cups, bowls, trays and hinged or lidded containers.
properties.Exceptions: NA
properties.Enforcement: Fine of $50. Statement purpose to educate rather than punish citizens.
